1: The LORDE is kynge, be the people neuer so vnpacient: he sytteth vpon the Cherubins, be the earth neuer so vnquiete.
2: The LORDE is greate in Sion, & hye aboue all people.
3: O let men geue thakes vnto thy greate & wonderful name, for it is holy.
4: The kynges power loueth iudgment, thou preparest equite, thou executest iudgmet & rightuousnes in Iacob.
5: O magnifie the LORDE or God, fall downe before his fote stole, for he his holy.
6: Moses & Aaron amonge his prestes, & Samuel amonge soch as call vpo his name: these called vpon the LORDE, & he herde the.
7: He spake vnto the out of the cloudy piler, for they kepte his testimonies, & the lawe that he gaue them.
8: Thou herdest the (o LORDE or God) thou forgauest the o God, & punyshedst their owne invencions.
9: O magnifie the LORDE oure God, and worshipe him vpo his holy hill, for the LORDE oure God is holy.
